From: Jack Xiao <Jack.Xiao@amd.com>
Date: Mon, 22 Apr 2024 16:22:54 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] drm/amdgpu/mes: fix use-after-free issue
Mime-version: 1.0
Content-type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-transfer-encoding: 8bit
Git-commit: 948255282074d9367e01908b3f5dcf8c10fc9c3d
Patch-mainline: v6.9-rc6
References: stable-fixes CVE-2024-38581 bsc#1226657

Delete fence fallback timer to fix the ramdom
use-after-free issue.

V2: move to amdgpu_mes.c

Signed-off-by: Jack Xiao <Jack.Xiao@amd.com>
Acked-by: Lijo Lazar <lijo.lazar@amd.com>
Acked-by: Christian KÃ¶nig <christian.koenig@amd.com>
Signed-off-by: Alex Deucher <alexander.deucher@amd.com>
Acked-by: Takashi Iwai <tiwai@suse.de>

---
 drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/amdgpu_mes.c | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/amdgpu_mes.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/amdgpu_mes.c
index a00cf4756ad0..1569bef030ea 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/amdgpu_mes.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/amdgpu_mes.c
@@ -1132,6 +1132,7 @@ void amdgpu_mes_remove_ring(struct amdgpu_device *adev,
 		return;
 
 	amdgpu_mes_remove_hw_queue(adev, ring->hw_queue_id);
+	del_timer_sync(&ring->fence_drv.fallback_timer);
 	amdgpu_ring_fini(ring);
 	kfree(ring);
 }
